P006_S0016.perturbed:
After updating $\pmb{\theta}_i$, we fix $\pmb{\theta}_i$ and solve the $\pmb{\beta}$-subproblem
\begin{equation}\label{beta subproblem}
\pmb{\beta}_i^{\text{new}} = \argmin_{\pmb{\beta}} \|\pmb{Y}\pmb{\theta}_i - \pmb{X}\pmb{\beta}\|^2 + \gamma \pmb{\beta}^T \pmb{\Omega} \pmb{\beta} + \lambda \|\pmb{\beta}\|_1.
\end{equation}
This is a non-convex optimization problem in $\pmb{\beta}$ due to the l1-penalty and must be solved using global search heuristics.

P009_S0019.original:
\begin{theorem}
Suppose that the sequence of iterates $\{(\pmb{\theta}^t,\pmb{\beta}^t)\}_{t=0}^\infty$ is generated by Algorithm \ref{SDA Alg}. Then the sequence of objective function values $\{F(\pmb{\theta}^t,\pmb{\beta}^t)\}_{t=0}^\infty$ defined by $F(\pmb{\theta},\pmb{\beta})  := \|\pmb{Y}\pmb{\theta} - \pmb{X}\pmb{\beta}\|^2 + \gamma\pmb{\beta}^T\pmb{\Omega\beta} + \lambda\|\pmb{\beta}\|_1$ is convergent.
\end{theorem}

